----
--The best is to go to the following site to following the installation instructions:
https://josm.openstreetmap.de/
----
--For ubuntu users with Trusty development version just follow the following steps in order:

--1. Edit the sources.list file by running the following command in the terminal:
sudo editor /etc/apt/sources.list

--2. Add the following line into the sources.list file:
deb http://josm.openstreetmap.de/apt trusty universe

--3. To check the development version name, use the following command:
lsb_release -c

--4. Download and register the public key:
wget -q https://josm.openstreetmap.de/josm-apt.key -O- | sudo apt-key add -

--5. Update the repository:
sudo apt-get update

--6. If installing not for the first time, then run:
sudo apt-get remove josm josm-plugins

--7. Install the JOSM:
sudo apt-get install josm

----
--In order to run the gui, run the following command from the terminal:
josm


